32:28.291 --> 32:29.291
That one.

32:29.708 --> 32:31.388
So Cassie,
when Charlie gets here,

32:31.416 --> 32:32.936
you're going to hand him the envelope.

32:33.000 --> 32:34.630
Why do I have to do it?

32:34.708 --> 32:38.748
Because Nicole is very good
at getting people to do things for her.

32:38.833 --> 32:40.293
That's not what this is.

32:40.375 --> 32:42.495
I wiped her butt
until she was nine years old.

32:42.583 --> 32:43.793
She's very seductive that way.

32:43.875 --> 32:46.665
No, Mom, legally,
I can't be the one who serves him.

32:46.750 --> 32:48.960
But still, what I'm saying is true.

32:49.041 --> 32:51.921
Do I have to actually hand him
the envelope?

32:52.000 --> 32:54.726
Yes, but I'm going to tell him in advance
that they're divorce papers.

32:54.750 --> 32:57.880
Nora says it doesn't have to be so formal.
Where's Henry?

32:58.166 --> 33:01.036
He's playing in the living room
with Sam, and Jules, and Molly.

33:01.125 --> 33:03.351
Let's get them upstairs.
Charlie's going to be here soon.

33:03.375 --> 33:04.415
Sam, go upstairs.

33:04.458 --> 33:06.708
So, I'll tell Charlie
what's happening,

33:06.791 --> 33:09.711
and, Cassie,
you then hand him the envelope.

33:09.791 --> 33:10.791
Okay...

33:11.208 --> 33:12.078
I just get nervous.

33:12.166 --> 33:14.376
Well, can you un-serve?

33:15.125 --> 33:17.535
- What do you mean? Like take it back?
- Yeah.

33:18.583 --> 33:19.923
- I think so.
- You should check.

33:20.000 --> 33:22.710
- In case we change our minds...
- I'm not going to change my mind.

33:22.791 --> 33:25.517
- ...or we feel too bad for him.
- Maybe in case I do something wrong.

33:25.541 --> 33:27.461
Now you're both
just making me feel bad, okay?

33:27.541 --> 33:28.921
Sorry, sorry, I'm nervous!

33:29.000 --> 33:30.790
Well, we all are.

33:30.916 --> 33:32.666
And we love Charlie.

33:32.750 --> 33:34.630
You have to stop loving him, Mom.

33:34.708 --> 33:36.538
You can't be friends with him anymore.

33:36.625 --> 33:39.035
Charlie and I have our own relationship...

33:39.125 --> 33:41.285
...independent of your marriage.

33:41.583 --> 33:43.083
Just like I'm still friends

33:43.166 --> 33:45.036
with Cassie's ex, Jeff.

33:45.125 --> 33:46.495
Are you still seeing Jeff?

33:46.875 --> 33:48.705
An occasional lunch.

33:48.791 --> 33:50.041
I can't believe you!

33:50.125 --> 33:51.955
He still wants his camera back,
by the way.

33:52.041 --> 33:55.171
Listen, nothing can be independent
of our marriage right now.

33:55.250 --> 33:58.290
I can't believe I even have to explain
this to you. Just be on my side, okay?

33:58.375 --> 33:59.745
- Okay.
- And...

34:00.333 --> 34:01.543
stop seeing Jeff!

34:03.291 --> 34:05.921
Cassie, you're the server.

34:06.000 --> 34:08.330
Just let me practice a few times.

34:08.708 --> 34:10.378
I was never a good auditioner.

34:10.458 --> 34:13.208
- That's because you wanted it too badly.
- It's not an audition.

34:13.291 --> 34:17.081
- I'll play Charlie.
- It's just my palms are so perspired.

34:17.208 --> 34:19.538
Sweetie, you're blotting the envelope.

34:19.625 --> 34:21.574
Maybe Nicole should play you.

34:21.666 --> 34:22.826
Did you really just say that?

34:22.916 --> 34:25.076
We don't need to practice.
This is not a performance.

34:25.166 --> 34:26.646
Did we finish the other wine already?

34:26.708 --> 34:27.809
Yeah.

34:27.833 --> 34:28.882
Oh!

34:28.958 --> 34:30.788
- Oh.
- Okay, let me get him.

34:30.875 --> 34:32.391
- Okay.
- You both go in the other room.

34:32.416 --> 34:35.166
Cassie, you make sure that Henry
goes upstairs with Molly and Jules.

34:35.250 --> 34:36.250
Happening now.

34:38.166 --> 34:40.126
- Mom!
- I'm getting my wine.

34:41.000 --> 34:41.830
What?

34:41.916 --> 34:43.666
Henry's pooping
in the bathroom downstairs.

34:43.750 --> 34:45.350
Can we transfer him to the one upstairs?

34:45.375 --> 34:47.745
- I think it's mid-poop.
- Just grab him when he comes out.

34:47.833 --> 34:49.043
- Cassie?
- What?

34:49.125 --> 34:52.455
I'm... I'm putting the envelope
over here by the toaster.

34:52.541 --> 34:53.670
Copy you.

34:59.958 --> 35:00.878
- Hi.
- Hi.

35:00.958 --> 35:03.128
- Where's Henry?
- Uh, he's pooping.

35:03.833 --> 35:04.833
Hi, Henry!

35:06.041 --> 35:07.421
Does this couch still open?

35:07.625 --> 35:08.625
Yeah.

35:08.833 --> 35:12.713
I got off the plane to a text, but don't
tell anyone yet. It's still a secret.

35:12.791 --> 35:13.881
Okay.

35:16.708 --> 35:18.628
I won a MacArthur grant.

35:19.041 --> 35:20.041
Charlie!

35:20.083 --> 35:21.673
Oh, my God, that's great!

35:21.750 --> 35:22.920
Congratulations.

35:23.000 --> 35:26.170
I'll say it because you can't,
it's the genius grant. You're a genius.

35:26.250 --> 35:28.250
Oh, I'm really happy for you.
You deserve it.

35:28.333 --> 35:30.833
It's yours too.
We did all of this together.

35:30.916 --> 35:31.916
Thank you, but...

35:32.541 --> 35:34.291
it's yours, Charlie, you enjoy it.

35:35.041 --> 35:36.171
I'm starving.

35:36.250 --> 35:38.410
It's good money,
and they parse it out over five years.

35:38.458 --> 35:41.018
But it means I can keep everyone
in the theater company employed,

35:41.083 --> 35:42.083
pay my credit card debt.

35:42.125 --> 35:43.285
So great.

35:43.375 --> 35:46.125
Of course, I went instantly to,
"It's all downhill from here.

35:46.208 --> 35:48.708
- Now my first Broadway play has to fail."
- No.

35:48.791 --> 35:50.791
We just started rehearsals again,
and I don't know.

35:50.833 --> 35:53.226
You always don't know at this point,
and then, it gets there.

35:53.250 --> 35:54.750
Do I? Because I don't remember.

35:54.833 --> 35:56.923
I know, it's true, it'll be great.

35:57.000 --> 35:58.500
Okay, I hope you're right.

35:59.041 --> 36:00.671
- Everyone says hi.
- Oh.

36:02.833 --> 36:04.503
Tell them hi. I miss everyone.

36:04.583 --> 36:06.583
You'll see them again
when you come back.

36:06.625 --> 36:08.785
A MacArthur, Broadway...

36:08.875 --> 36:10.285
It's so exciting.

36:10.833 --> 36:12.503
Congratulations, Charlie.

36:19.291 --> 36:20.331
Which bathroom?

36:22.041 --> 36:23.541
- What?
- Is he pooping?

36:24.500 --> 36:26.000
Oh, uh, downstairs.

36:26.166 --> 36:27.166
Is your mom home?

36:27.833 --> 36:28.923
Yeah, she's upstairs.

36:32.166 --> 36:33.926
- Hey, how's it going?
- Nothing yet.

36:33.958 --> 36:35.248
- It's me.
- I know.

36:35.750 --> 36:37.290
- I just got here.
- Hi.

36:37.375 --> 36:38.975
- I brought you something.
- Yay.

36:39.041 --> 36:40.711
Mom's getting me a present too.

36:41.000 --> 36:42.880
- Why?
- For pooping.

36:44.083 --> 36:45.083
Oh.

36:46.875 --> 36:48.535
- I love you.
- I love you.

36:49.250 --> 36:51.580
I don't think we should reward him
for pooping anymore.

36:51.666 --> 36:53.996
Oh, I know, but he holds it in
and it's going on a week.

36:54.083 --> 36:56.753
- It's its own reward. G-ma!
- Charlie-bird!

36:56.833 --> 36:58.713
Oh! No! Stop it!

36:58.791 --> 37:00.421
Oh, God, I'm huge!

37:00.500 --> 37:02.580
- You're as light as a feather.
- Mom?

37:03.583 --> 37:07.003
- Why didn't you respond to my last email?
- Well, your emails are so articulate.

37:07.083 --> 37:08.683
I get intimidated.

37:08.750 --> 37:11.000
- Mom, can you...
- Now, I'm going to lift you!

37:11.083 --> 37:13.673
Mom?

37:13.750 --> 37:14.750
Mom?

37:15.833 --> 37:17.083
- Mom?
- What?

37:17.166 --> 37:18.246
Upstairs.

37:18.333 --> 37:19.793
Oh.

37:19.875 --> 37:21.575
I'm going to write you back now.

37:25.541 --> 37:26.711
Cassie?

37:27.458 --> 37:28.458
Hey, Charlie.

37:28.541 --> 37:29.791
I like your haircut.

37:30.250 --> 37:31.250
Oh, thanks.

37:33.083 --> 37:34.423
- Mom?
- I'll go.

37:34.958 --> 37:36.828
Henry's calling you, Nicole!

37:36.916 --> 37:37.916
I hear him.

37:38.875 --> 37:40.325
What's going on, Henry?

37:40.416 --> 37:42.036
Can you ask Mom to come?

37:44.041 --> 37:45.041
He wants you.

37:48.250 --> 37:49.500
What kind of pie is that?

37:52.125 --> 37:53.125
It's...

37:57.708 --> 37:58.708
pecan.

38:00.041 --> 38:01.751
- Did you make it?
- I don't know.

38:02.416 --> 38:03.536
No, it's store bought.

38:04.250 --> 38:05.500
You know Joan's on Third?

38:05.583 --> 38:07.633
- Oh, yeah. It's good, right?
- What?

38:07.916 --> 38:09.076
The store? Yeah.

38:10.166 --> 38:11.416
Jules and Molly love it.

38:11.500 --> 38:12.920
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

38:13.833 --> 38:15.083
I'm just hot!

38:16.500 --> 38:17.880
Uh, I'll pour you some water.

38:19.375 --> 38:20.995
Nicole says you're doing a play?

38:21.125 --> 38:22.625
I-I think you'd like it.

38:22.708 --> 38:26.288
It's a great unproduced play
by this really interesting British writer.

38:26.875 --> 38:28.726
- So, you do an English accent?
- Yeah.

38:28.750 --> 38:30.790
- It's more northern England.
- Oh.

38:30.875 --> 38:31.995
What does that sound like?

38:33.916 --> 38:36.876
Ooh, you want a cup of tea, do ya?

38:38.416 --> 38:40.036
Right. Good.

38:41.375 --> 38:44.745
Oh, thank you, missus. What is...

38:45.708 --> 38:46.788
What's this?

38:46.833 --> 38:49.003
Oh, it's a manila envelope, love.

38:49.083 --> 38:51.476
- Ooh, can I start over?
- It has my name on it.

38:51.500 --> 38:52.500
Ooh.

38:56.333 --> 38:57.333
Oh.

38:57.708 --> 38:58.788
Jesus.

38:58.916 --> 39:01.246
Sorry. You're served.

39:03.375 --> 39:05.125
- What did you do?
- Nothing. I don't know.

39:05.625 --> 39:07.245
I can't lie.

39:07.333 --> 39:08.793
You're being served.

39:08.875 --> 39:11.625
You guys are getting a div...
I don't know, I'm sorry.

39:17.958 --> 39:20.708
I was going to warn you
so it didn't become a thing. I'm sorry.

39:34.208 --> 39:35.578
I feel like I'm in a dream.

39:37.333 --> 39:39.003
We don't have a marriage anymore.

39:39.083 --> 39:42.713
I-I know you don't want the disruption,
but you don't want to be married.

39:43.000 --> 39:44.630
Not... really.

39:46.833 --> 39:48.043
But I don't want this.

39:50.875 --> 39:53.205
What did you expect was going to happen?

39:56.500 --> 39:59.250
I... I don't know,
I guess I didn't think it through,

39:59.333 --> 40:02.883
but I thought we agreed
we weren't going to use lawyers.

40:03.333 --> 40:04.673
I want...

40:05.250 --> 40:08.790
I don't know, I'm trying to say this
as undramatically as possible.

40:08.875 --> 40:10.035
I want...

40:11.666 --> 40:13.706
an entirely different kind of life.

40:14.500 --> 40:17.130
Let's wait until you finish this pilot
and come back to New York.

40:17.208 --> 40:19.208
Let's figure it out there,
at home, together.

40:19.291 --> 40:22.226
- Nora's known for being very fair.
- We don't need to do it with envelopes.

40:22.250 --> 40:23.080
- This is Nora?
- Yeah.

40:23.166 --> 40:25.286
She's great. I feel like
we could be friends with her.

40:25.333 --> 40:28.583
- Why do I feel like that won't happen?
- It's just a formality.

40:28.666 --> 40:30.476
- Why...
- You don't have to respond right away.

40:30.500 --> 40:32.000
Why did Cassie have a pie?

40:32.333 --> 40:34.883
The pie was hers.
The pie wasn't part of it.

40:34.958 --> 40:35.788
Are you sure?

40:35.875 --> 40:38.075
I mean, what would the pie
have to do with anything?

40:38.166 --> 40:40.576
I don't know. It somehow makes it worse.

40:41.458 --> 40:43.788
I'm sorry, but the pie was just a pie.

40:44.833 --> 40:45.883
So, what...

40:48.916 --> 40:49.996
What do I do?

40:52.708 --> 40:53.878
You get a lawyer too.

40:57.791 --> 40:59.921
"Well, I guess
I better be going.

41:00.000 --> 41:03.250
Stuart rose from the ditch,
climbed into his car...

41:04.000 --> 41:06.460
and started up the road
that led toward the north.

41:07.375 --> 41:10.125
The sun was just coming up
over the hills on his right.

41:11.083 --> 41:14.583
As he peered ahead into the great land
that stretched before him,

41:15.125 --> 41:16.455
the way seemed long...

41:17.500 --> 41:18.790
but the sky was bright.

41:19.625 --> 41:22.495
And he somehow felt
he was headed in the right direction."

41:25.250 --> 41:27.130
I forgot it ended that way.

41:28.500 --> 41:31.670
Yeah, wow, Stuart really overreacted,
didn't you think?

41:32.416 --> 41:34.166
He was upset about his boat.

41:38.500 --> 41:40.040
Dad, you go away.

41:41.083 --> 41:43.043
Mom, you stay.

41:43.416 --> 41:46.376
- Hey, Daddy just got here.
- It's okay.

41:47.791 --> 41:48.791
Love you.

41:52.375 --> 41:56.785
You can come back, and wake me up,
and read to me later, Daddy, okay?

41:57.291 --> 41:58.291
Okay.

42:00.666 --> 42:02.876
Will you come sleep
in my bed later?

42:02.958 --> 42:03.958
Yeah.

42:13.125 --> 42:14.125
Oh.

42:14.500 --> 42:16.460
Hang in there, Charlie-bird.

42:16.625 --> 42:17.625
Thanks, G-ma.

42:47.291 --> 42:49.581
- He's in a mommy phase right now.
- It's okay.

42:58.916 --> 42:59.746
Whoo!

42:59.833 --> 43:01.923
I'm sorry. I drank too much wine.

43:02.333 --> 43:04.043
- I can imagine.
- And didn't eat dinner.

43:04.125 --> 43:05.455
Stressful time.

43:06.500 --> 43:07.750
I hope Henry didn't notice.

43:07.833 --> 43:08.833
I'm sure he didn't.

43:08.875 --> 43:10.555
Now that I'm a parent,
I realize my parents

43:10.583 --> 43:12.223
were probably drunk all the time with me.

43:12.250 --> 43:13.250
Yeah.

43:13.291 --> 43:14.461
I'm sorry again.

43:16.250 --> 43:17.250
Thanks.

43:18.333 --> 43:19.463
Where are you staying?

43:23.041 --> 43:24.831
Oh, well, I...

43:26.375 --> 43:27.415
hadn't...

43:31.583 --> 43:32.583
I guess I'll...

43:34.958 --> 43:37.248
There's a new hotel on Highland that's...

43:38.083 --> 43:41.543
supposedly not too expensive
and... and pretty nice.

43:41.958 --> 43:43.668
Oh, okay, I'll check it out.

43:44.250 --> 43:46.540
Again, that's great
about the MacArthur.

43:46.916 --> 43:47.916
Thanks.

43:55.500 --> 43:57.000
- Charlie?
- Yeah?

44:00.708 --> 44:01.708
Thanks.

44:08.916 --> 44:09.746
Fuck.

44:09.833 --> 44:13.083
- What?
- She's being represented by Nora.

44:13.166 --> 44:14.576
She's supposedly very fair?

44:14.666 --> 44:16.456
All right, here's the fact, Jack.

44:17.083 --> 44:20.083
I charge $950 an hour.

44:20.166 --> 44:21.626
Ted is 400.

44:22.083 --> 44:24.753
If you have a stupid question,
you call Ted.

44:26.333 --> 44:29.083
To start, we'll need a $25,000 retainer.

44:29.166 --> 44:31.184
- That's more than I can...
- And all your financials.

44:31.208 --> 44:32.748
We need to do a forensic accounting.

44:32.833 --> 44:36.333
Which runs anywhere
from ten to twenty thousand dollars.

44:37.041 --> 44:39.671
But if we can all agree right away,
it shouldn't get too bad,

44:39.750 --> 44:42.080
- right?
- You were married here in LA?

44:42.166 --> 44:44.456
Yes... because her mom and sister
are out here

44:44.541 --> 44:47.211
- and I'm not close with my family.
- Your son was born out here?

44:47.291 --> 44:50.791
Yes, because, again, her mom
and sister are out here and I'm not...

44:50.875 --> 44:52.415
So, you got married here,

44:52.500 --> 44:54.250
your kid was born here...

44:55.833 --> 44:57.133
and she served you here?

44:57.208 --> 44:58.998
Yeah, but we lived in New York.

45:00.000 --> 45:01.000
Why?

45:02.333 --> 45:04.833
- Is there a problem?
- We'll have to reshape the narrative.

45:04.916 --> 45:08.746
If you're serious
about having your child in New York,

45:08.833 --> 45:10.463
this is what I suggest.

45:10.541 --> 45:13.421
You take your kid...
D-Did you say his name was Fred?

45:14.166 --> 45:14.996
Henry.

45:15.083 --> 45:16.003
Henry?

45:16.083 --> 45:17.293
Why did I say Fred?

45:17.375 --> 45:18.875
I have a kid named Fred.

45:18.958 --> 45:22.498
You take Henry to New York
with you right now.

45:22.583 --> 45:24.883
Then we file an action in New York.

45:25.166 --> 45:26.326
We make this a New York case.

45:26.375 --> 45:28.892
We need to make an argument
that you're a New York-based family.

45:28.916 --> 45:29.746
Well, we are.

45:29.833 --> 45:32.753
Otherwise, you'll probably never
see your kid outside of LA again.

45:32.833 --> 45:34.503
Really? No.

45:34.583 --> 45:37.793
It's very hard
to convince the courts to move a kid.

45:37.875 --> 45:41.075
As soon as you let your wife and child
leave New York,

45:41.166 --> 45:43.996
you made life very difficult for yourself.

45:44.083 --> 45:45.333
Yes, but as I said,

45:45.416 --> 45:47.876
we're a New York family,
that's just a fact.

45:48.750 --> 45:50.750
She's... here temporarily.

45:51.208 --> 45:53.628
Then why do you think
she served you out here?

45:54.291 --> 45:58.421
I don't... know,
but Henry wants to go back to New York.

45:58.500 --> 46:00.460
Don't quote your kid.

46:01.250 --> 46:03.420
He's just telling you
what you want to hear.

46:04.208 --> 46:07.168
And trust me,
he's telling her the opposite.

46:07.250 --> 46:08.750
Let me have the Barber file!

46:08.833 --> 46:10.043
It's right here.

46:10.416 --> 46:12.036
Move my lunch to 1:30.

46:16.625 --> 46:17.625
What's...

46:19.625 --> 46:21.165
"Exit Goat"?

46:21.583 --> 46:24.213
Exit Ghost. It's the name
of my theater company.

46:24.291 --> 46:25.291
You're a director?

46:25.541 --> 46:27.081
Theater director, yeah.

46:27.166 --> 46:29.876
- Anything I've seen?
- I don't know. What have you seen?

46:32.458 --> 46:34.538
Our production of Electra
is moving to Broadway...

46:35.791 --> 46:36.631
which is exciting.

46:36.708 --> 46:38.918
We have to make sure
that money is protected.

46:39.083 --> 46:41.633
I mean, it's theater,
so it's not a lot of money.

46:41.708 --> 46:44.748
I basically put whatever money I make
back in the theater.

46:44.833 --> 46:47.793
I wonder, do we ask for support?

46:48.250 --> 46:49.920
- Interesting.
- From Nicole?

46:50.000 --> 46:51.380
I'm not going to do that.

46:51.875 --> 46:53.495
Does your wife's family have money?

46:54.500 --> 46:57.710
Uh, her mother has some
from her TV career.

46:57.791 --> 46:59.131
And her father died.

46:59.208 --> 47:03.628
Well, we could say that we don't want
her mother to see the kid,

47:03.958 --> 47:05.288
draw her into the case.

47:05.375 --> 47:08.495
In that instance,
her mother could pay your legal fees.

47:08.958 --> 47:09.958
No.

47:10.583 --> 47:12.003
I'm very close to her mom.

47:12.375 --> 47:15.335
- Nicole's family has been my family...
- Yeah, but that's going to change.

47:15.375 --> 47:17.205
And I suggest you get used to it.

47:17.916 --> 47:21.746
- We need to hire a private investigator.
- Really? I mean...

47:23.291 --> 47:25.831
- Really?
- Does your wife do drugs or anything?

47:25.916 --> 47:26.916
Coke?

47:27.500 --> 47:28.580
Not in any real way.

47:28.958 --> 47:31.668
Well, we're not going to win
if she's the perfect mother.

47:31.750 --> 47:33.630
She was addicted to Tums for a while.

47:35.083 --> 47:38.213
It wasn't nothing.
She was up to a tube a day.

47:38.291 --> 47:40.081
Have you noticed anyone following you?

47:40.166 --> 47:41.166
No.

47:42.375 --> 47:43.745
Well, keep an eye out.

47:43.833 --> 47:46.003
Look, you need to be prepared for the fact

47:46.083 --> 47:50.173
that Nora is going to portray you
as a neglectful, absent father.

47:50.666 --> 47:52.876
- But I'm not.
- You live in New York.

47:52.958 --> 47:54.628
You're consumed with your work.

47:55.125 --> 47:58.535
She and your kid are out here, struggling.

47:58.625 --> 48:01.995
Nora's going to use that strategy.
I'm sure of it.

48:02.083 --> 48:03.283
But Nicole's not going to lie.

48:03.333 --> 48:06.213
Listen, if we start from a place
of reasonable,

48:06.291 --> 48:08.581
and they start from a place of crazy,

48:08.666 --> 48:12.706
when we settle, we'll be somewhere
between reasonable and crazy.

48:12.791 --> 48:13.671
Which is still crazy.

48:13.750 --> 48:15.330
Half of crazy is crazy.

48:15.416 --> 48:18.476
You know what people say, "Criminal
lawyers see bad people at their best,

48:18.500 --> 48:20.580
divorce lawyers see good people
at their worst."

48:20.666 --> 48:23.496
Before this is all over,
you're going to hate me and Ted,

48:23.583 --> 48:26.213
just because of what we represent
in your life.

48:26.291 --> 48:27.291
I'm sure you're right.

48:27.375 --> 48:29.875
So tell me the story again.
You came out here to see your kid.

48:29.958 --> 48:32.101
- Maybe I'm not explaining this well.
- She serves you.

48:32.125 --> 48:33.809
- We're friendly, we're fine.
- What a bitch.

48:33.833 --> 48:36.017
We're just trying to figure this out.
She's not a bitch.

48:36.041 --> 48:37.291
Thanks, but this isn't...

48:37.375 --> 48:38.705
We're doing it a different way.

48:39.083 --> 48:41.793
And... I can't even close to afford this.

48:42.166 --> 48:46.036
I've got to get back to New York.
I have a Broadway play in rehearsals.

48:50.291 --> 48:53.751
I was the hot shit at that time.

48:53.833 --> 48:58.793
Young, very sexy,
with a great head of hair.

48:58.875 --> 49:01.495
I just so appreciate that Charlie
gave me this opportunity.

49:01.583 --> 49:03.003
Or maybe I should thank Nicole.

49:03.083 --> 49:05.633
I heard Nicole's pilot went to series,
so she's moving to LA.

49:05.708 --> 49:07.288
And they put Henry in school out there.

49:07.375 --> 49:08.575
Well, is Charlie moving too?

49:08.666 --> 49:09.746
Not Charlie.

49:09.833 --> 49:11.043
He won't abandon us.

49:11.125 --> 49:12.745
And you can't do theater in LA.

49:12.833 --> 49:15.213
Charlie said she and Henry
are coming back to New York

49:15.291 --> 49:17.041
when she finishes filming her show.

49:17.125 --> 49:18.535
I wouldn't be so sure.

49:18.625 --> 49:21.535
Nicole was never going to stay
in New York, that was obvious.

49:21.625 --> 49:23.625
She was probably
planning this move all along.

49:23.708 --> 49:27.038
When she sees an opportunity,
believe me, she takes it.

49:27.125 --> 49:29.245
Well, LA is nice.

49:29.666 --> 49:30.576
The space.

49:30.666 --> 49:33.826
Miss Four Time Oscar winner, sucking my...

49:33.916 --> 49:35.996
Okay, how is everyone today?

49:36.083 --> 49:38.293
Nobody get too close.
I think I caught Donna's cold.

49:38.375 --> 49:41.125
- Sorry, Charlie.
- I'm expecting a Skype call from Henry,

49:41.208 --> 49:42.918
so I might have to step out.

49:44.125 --> 49:46.455
So, Charlie, what you're going through now

49:46.541 --> 49:49.831
is going to be horrible,
but it will be over.

49:49.916 --> 49:51.076
Thanks, Frank.

49:51.458 --> 49:52.668
- Another thing.
- Yeah?

49:53.166 --> 49:57.286
Fuck as many people
as you can right now.

49:57.375 --> 49:59.575
Women, men.

50:00.250 --> 50:02.809
- Take what I said seriously.
- You might need help wrapping gauze.

50:02.833 --> 50:05.543
- It needs to stay tight.
- Okay, I'm... I'm confused.

50:05.625 --> 50:07.785
What... scene
is the Invisible Man outfit for?

50:07.875 --> 50:09.825
No, that's my Halloween costume.

50:09.916 --> 50:12.456
And the Frankenstein
is for Henry.

50:14.208 --> 50:15.408
He's coming here this weekend.

50:15.458 --> 50:17.328
We're going to trick or treat
in the Slope.

50:17.416 --> 50:19.706
I made it more James Whale
than Kenneth Branagh.

50:19.791 --> 50:21.541
- Perfect.
- Can I talk to you?

50:22.250 --> 50:23.960
Yeah, over...

50:24.625 --> 50:26.995
I've typed up the blocking
from the last two rehearsals,

50:27.083 --> 50:30.883
and here are the director notes
from that Danish production from the '70s.

50:31.958 --> 50:32.878
Where'd you find it?

50:32.958 --> 50:35.538
- The library, duh.
- Ha!

50:35.875 --> 50:37.075
Can I come over tonight?

50:38.416 --> 50:40.326
Mary Ann, it's too hard now.

50:40.416 --> 50:42.496
I just can't be with anyone right now.

50:42.583 --> 50:45.503
But we did it when you were married
and we shouldn't have done it.

50:45.583 --> 50:47.851
And now that you're not married,
shouldn't we be doing it?

50:47.875 --> 50:50.915
I'm not not married yet.

50:51.375 --> 50:53.125
You're torturing yourself.

50:53.375 --> 50:55.285
Just make sure
everything doesn't go to hell.

50:56.541 --> 50:58.541
- I'm relying on you, okay?
- Fine.

50:58.625 --> 51:01.205
- Thanks.
- I wish you'd accept generosity better.

51:01.291 --> 51:02.541
Uh, hold on. Let me...

51:03.000 --> 51:04.920
- Hello?
- Is this Charlie Barber?

51:05.416 --> 51:06.246
Yes.

51:06.333 --> 51:08.133
Hi, this is Nora Fanshaw.

51:08.208 --> 51:10.078
I represent your wife, Nicole Barber.

51:10.166 --> 51:12.246
- Hi.
- Do you have an attorney yet?

51:12.333 --> 51:13.173
No.

51:13.250 --> 51:15.809
Okay, then it's okay for me
to talk to you directly, okay?

51:15.833 --> 51:16.833
Okay.

51:17.166 --> 51:20.326
I'm calling because we haven't
received your response to our filing.

51:20.750 --> 51:23.880
Yeah, I've been rehearsing this play
and flying back and forth to LA.

51:23.958 --> 51:26.038
You're going to need
to file your response.

51:28.000 --> 51:30.750
- Nicole said there was no rush.
- It's been more than 30 days

51:30.833 --> 51:31.833
since you were served.

51:31.916 --> 51:33.756
By law, you're meant to respond
within 30 days.

51:33.791 --> 51:35.271
I didn't like the first lawyer I met.

51:35.333 --> 51:37.851
It says that very clearly
on the document you were given.

51:37.875 --> 51:38.745
Did you read it?

51:38.833 --> 51:40.593
Yeah, but I thought
that's just what it says.

51:40.666 --> 51:42.416
We weren't even going to do it
with lawyers.

51:43.416 --> 51:45.666
Charlie, I think I shouldn't
tuck in my shirt.

51:45.750 --> 51:48.726
- Nicole said I could take my time.
- And we've let you take your time.

51:48.750 --> 51:51.934
- It comes out during the love scene.
- Could you hold a second? What love scene?

51:51.958 --> 51:53.288
When I hug Beth.

51:53.416 --> 51:54.416
You don't hug Beth.

51:54.458 --> 51:56.788
I think it's something we should explore.

51:56.875 --> 51:59.745
Can't you just tuck it in tighter
or get Donna to safety pin it?

51:59.833 --> 52:01.713
I also have a kind of a thing

52:01.791 --> 52:04.131
- about, uh, tucking things in.
- Charlie?

52:04.416 --> 52:05.746
If you don't file your response,

52:05.833 --> 52:08.313
we're going to file a request
for default judgment against you.

52:08.666 --> 52:11.206
...insecurities about my figure.

52:11.291 --> 52:12.501
- Charlie?
- Yes, sorry.

52:12.583 --> 52:14.753
Default judgment, what does that mean?
Don't hug Beth.

52:14.833 --> 52:16.934
We'll be able to lay claim
to whatever we want.

52:16.958 --> 52:18.828
W-What do you mean,
whatever you want of what?

52:18.916 --> 52:21.326
Your apartment, your things,
everything you own.

52:21.416 --> 52:22.246
We...

52:22.333 --> 52:25.173
She and I already discussed this.
We don't own that much stuff.

52:25.250 --> 52:26.970
She can have
pretty much whatever she wants.

52:27.000 --> 52:30.101
And it means we'll set the number
for child support at its highest level

52:30.125 --> 52:31.995
and claim full custody of your child.

52:34.083 --> 52:35.083
Full custody?

52:36.833 --> 52:39.463
- I mean, that's not even...
- This is what the law says.

52:40.416 --> 52:43.206
Nicole's not going to do that.
I mean, she won't.

52:43.541 --> 52:45.291
No, Charlie, I represent Nicole,

52:45.375 --> 52:47.665
and she's aware of everything
I'm saying to you.

52:47.750 --> 52:49.070
I just spoke to her this morning.

52:49.125 --> 52:52.325
Well, I spoke to her five minutes
before I got on the call.

52:55.750 --> 52:56.750
Okay, so what do I do?

52:56.833 --> 52:59.133
You need to get a lawyer
and respond immediately.

52:59.208 --> 53:02.578
Nicole wants to do this amicably,
but you're leaving us no other option.

53:02.666 --> 53:04.416
I'll get a lawyer.
Can I get a lawyer here?

53:04.500 --> 53:06.460
- I don't know where "here" is.
- New York.

53:06.541 --> 53:08.881
Ah!
That's what all that honking is?

53:09.583 --> 53:11.623
No, you'll have to come to LA
and meet people in LA.

53:11.666 --> 53:12.666
I'm rehearsing a...

53:12.708 --> 53:16.038
If you don't respond in Los Angeles
by Friday, you'll leave us no choice.

53:16.125 --> 53:17.745
Wh... Which line?

53:18.416 --> 53:21.126
I have to take this.
Can you hold on a second, Charlie?

53:47.916 --> 53:51.036
Me and Mommy are in the middle
of a super secret treasure hunt.

53:52.041 --> 53:54.581
- I thought the plane landed at nine.
- What are you wearing?

53:54.666 --> 53:55.666
Sock pants.

53:55.833 --> 53:57.423
It did. What are sock pants?

53:57.500 --> 53:59.420
He doesn't like to feel the breeze
on his legs.

53:59.500 --> 54:00.330
He dressed himself.

54:00.416 --> 54:02.767
- There are long pants. Can I talk to you?
- It's almost noon.

54:02.791 --> 54:04.671
There was traffic. We've got to get going.

54:04.750 --> 54:07.434
- Why don't we ever do a treasure hunt?
- Henry, can you wait a minute?

54:07.458 --> 54:08.708
No talking alone.

54:08.791 --> 54:11.001
Just one bit of talking alone,
then I'll be right there.

54:11.541 --> 54:12.831
I got a call from your lawyer.

54:12.916 --> 54:15.416
She said you'd take everything and...

54:16.500 --> 54:18.500
custody and everything
if I didn't respond.

54:18.583 --> 54:20.423
It's better if we just
let the lawyers do this.

54:20.458 --> 54:22.578
Yeah, but she's saying things
I don't think you mean.

54:22.666 --> 54:24.326
Henry, we need to get going.

54:24.416 --> 54:25.876
I don't want to go now.

54:25.958 --> 54:28.309
- Have you gotten a lawyer yet?
- That's what I'm here to do.

54:28.333 --> 54:29.883
Come on, Henry. I'm in a rush.

54:29.958 --> 54:31.128
I have three more clues.

54:31.208 --> 54:33.809
Why did you start a treasure hunt
or whatever so close to my arrival?

54:33.833 --> 54:35.923
- Cool
- You were late. We were killing time.

54:36.000 --> 54:38.380
Honey, come. We're going to finish
the treasure hunt later.

54:38.458 --> 54:40.038
- I'm going to be rich!
- Okay.

54:40.125 --> 54:42.351
You're going to go with your daddy,
it's going to be fun.

54:42.375 --> 54:45.625
And I've got a present for you
when you get back as a reward.

54:46.500 --> 54:47.700
He's not going to the dentist.

54:47.750 --> 54:49.710
- I'm trying to help.
- I'm staying here.

54:49.791 --> 54:50.791
Come on.

54:54.625 --> 54:55.625
Henry?

55:01.083 --> 55:03.583
- Got the booster?
- I have a booster.

55:05.375 --> 55:06.995
Oh, wait, no, it's not in.

55:07.375 --> 55:08.375
What's not in?

55:08.708 --> 55:10.708
The seat's not connected.

55:13.833 --> 55:15.503
I asked the rental company to install it.

55:15.583 --> 55:18.333
Yeah, I think they can't
for liability reasons.

55:18.583 --> 55:20.809
- Do you know how these things...
- Let me just... If you...

55:20.833 --> 55:23.543
- There should be a clip to clip onto.
- ...dig...

55:28.291 --> 55:29.831
Ow! Fuck!

55:29.916 --> 55:31.706
- Why "fuck?"
- Something sharp.

55:31.791 --> 55:33.171
- Can't I stay with Mom?
- No.

55:33.250 --> 55:34.290
Why not?

55:34.375 --> 55:36.375
It's my time with you.
I just flew 3,000 miles.

55:36.458 --> 55:37.328
I don't want to.

55:37.416 --> 55:38.916
Henry, get in the fucking car!

55:41.083 --> 55:43.333
I'm sorry, but Jesus,
get in the fucking car.

55:48.416 --> 55:50.576
How do you spell Lego Bionicles?

55:50.666 --> 55:53.036
That's two words.
What does Lego start with?

55:53.125 --> 55:54.165
Just tell me.

55:54.250 --> 55:55.559
- Don't you want to learn it?
- No.

55:55.583 --> 55:56.963
- It's on the box, anyway.
- L...

55:57.041 --> 55:58.041
Then what?

55:58.208 --> 56:00.998
E... You know,
everyone at the theater says hi.

56:01.083 --> 56:02.003
Hi.

56:02.083 --> 56:02.963
Then what?

56:03.041 --> 56:04.581
A "g-g-g" sound.

56:04.666 --> 56:06.626
- Are you excited for Halloween?
- J?

56:06.708 --> 56:07.538
G.

56:07.625 --> 56:09.285
- Then what?
- And an "O" sound.

56:09.375 --> 56:11.495
- O?
- Are you excited for Halloween?

56:11.583 --> 56:12.503
Yeah.

56:12.583 --> 56:14.083
I brought both our costumes.

56:14.166 --> 56:16.456
I'm going as a store-bought ninja.

56:16.541 --> 56:18.671
But we agreed.
I had Donna make you a Frankenstein.

56:18.750 --> 56:20.920
I don't want to be a Frankenstein anymore.

56:21.000 --> 56:22.000
Are you sure?

56:23.666 --> 56:24.706
Maybe just look at it.

56:25.250 --> 56:27.880
It's awesome. We'll be Frankenstein
and the Invisible Man.

56:27.958 --> 56:29.958
Mom bought me a ninja costume,

56:30.166 --> 56:32.746
which is better because it costs more.

56:32.833 --> 56:34.423
Technically, the Frankenstein cost more

56:34.500 --> 56:36.630
when you factor in Donna's time
and the materials.

56:36.708 --> 56:38.958
The cousins are also going to be ninjas.

56:39.041 --> 56:40.881
But Henry,
we went through all this trouble.

56:44.500 --> 56:45.540
Okay.

56:45.625 --> 56:46.625
Whatever you want.

56:51.166 --> 56:53.876
Please take the ticket.

56:58.000 --> 56:59.892
- Dad, you're too far.
- I know.

56:59.916 --> 57:02.576
Please take the ticket.

57:09.291 --> 57:11.581
So, I'm not comfortable
leaving the bags in the car

57:11.666 --> 57:13.851
where I've given the key to someone
I don't really know.

57:13.875 --> 57:14.875
I've been here.

57:15.125 --> 57:18.455
It's an office building,
so you've been to places like this before.

57:19.000 --> 57:20.580
I remember those fish.

57:21.708 --> 57:23.128
A lot of fish look the same.

57:23.708 --> 57:24.708
Can I help you?

57:24.750 --> 57:27.250
I'm Charlie Barber.
I have a 1:30 with Dan Cohen.

57:27.333 --> 57:29.083
Oh, hi. Where's your little man?

57:29.166 --> 57:32.326
I don't have it this time.
I keep my skeletons at my mom's.

57:32.708 --> 57:33.708
Okay.

57:35.041 --> 57:36.041
Oh, okay.

57:36.250 --> 57:38.170
I'm sorry. We tried to reach you.

57:38.250 --> 57:40.040
Mr. Cohen wanted me to apologize.

57:40.125 --> 57:43.285
He can't see you because apparently
your wife already met with him

57:43.375 --> 57:45.625
on the 7th of August about representation.

57:46.291 --> 57:47.791
B-But she hired somebody else.

57:47.875 --> 57:50.205
- Uh... Nora...
- Fanshaw?

57:50.500 --> 57:53.020
But unfortunately, because she consulted
with Mr. Cohen already,

57:53.083 --> 57:55.083
he's legally barred from representing you.

57:55.791 --> 57:56.631
Oh.

57:56.708 --> 57:58.348
- Should we feed the fish?
- Yeah.

57:58.958 --> 58:01.378
- It happens all the time.
- Really?

58:01.458 --> 58:03.748
If you have a ticket,
I can validate your parking.

58:04.291 --> 58:05.291
Oh.

58:05.375 --> 58:08.434
You know, it's common that people
meet with as many lawyers as possible

58:08.458 --> 58:10.378
so that their spouse has limited options.

58:10.458 --> 58:12.498
Oh, I don't think
she would've done it deliberately.

58:12.541 --> 58:13.921
You'd be surprised.

58:14.166 --> 58:16.706
Can all of them, like,
breathe out of the water?

58:18.416 --> 58:20.496
Did you go to a lot of offices
with your mom?

58:20.583 --> 58:21.713
Not so many.

58:23.333 --> 58:24.333
Like 11.

58:24.708 --> 58:27.248
I don't think anyone
would have stealed the bags, Daddy.

58:27.333 --> 58:28.503
I need somebody today.

58:28.583 --> 58:31.293
If I don't respond by tomorrow,
she said I could lose custody.

58:31.375 --> 58:34.267
I didn't know who else to call.
There's got to be someone she didn't meet.

58:34.291 --> 58:35.421
I have a name for you.

58:36.458 --> 58:38.328
Bert Spitz.

58:38.875 --> 58:42.165
He was the entertainment lawyer
at Roberto's agency.

58:42.625 --> 58:43.455
Great.

58:43.541 --> 58:47.001
But then he kind of got pushed
into retirement a few years ago,

58:47.291 --> 58:49.081
and he went into family law.

58:49.166 --> 58:50.996
- I called him.
- Thank you, G-ma.

58:51.083 --> 58:53.753
- He can see you today at three.
- Aw, shit.

58:54.416 --> 58:56.956
We never had this conversation,
Charlie-bird.

58:57.041 --> 58:58.392
You got it. I love you.

58:58.416 --> 58:59.416
- Aw.
- Dad!

58:59.458 --> 59:02.038
- I need a new burger.
- Why?

59:02.125 --> 59:06.415
Because you made us carry your bags
into the restaurant, I dropped it.

59:07.916 --> 59:10.286
That's fine. I'll give you mine.
Get in the car.

59:10.375 --> 59:13.325
Why did you bring me today
if you couldn't hang out with me?

59:13.416 --> 59:15.326
Because I've been away
and want to see you.

59:16.083 --> 59:19.383
Jamie Tuber has a little sister

59:19.458 --> 59:21.958
named, um, Lily Tuber.

59:22.041 --> 59:24.331
- Yeah.
- And Lily Tuber is really bossy.

59:24.416 --> 59:25.416
Uh-huh.

59:26.583 --> 59:30.333
Getting divorced with a kid can be
one of the hardest things you'll ever do.

59:32.000 --> 59:33.880
It's like a death without a body.

59:36.041 --> 59:39.331
I know personally.
I've been there four different times.

59:39.416 --> 59:41.036
You've been divorced four times?

59:41.125 --> 59:42.245
Married four times.

59:42.666 --> 59:43.826
Three divorces.

59:44.875 --> 59:47.205
This last one will stick, God willing.

59:47.291 --> 59:49.671
That's why I graduated into family law,

59:49.958 --> 59:52.208
to help people survive this painful time.

59:53.958 --> 59:55.168
Here's how I see it.

59:56.583 --> 59:59.543
If we get bogged down
in "who did this," and "who did that,"

59:59.625 --> 01:00:01.305
and "I don't want to pay the two dollars,"

01:00:01.333 --> 01:00:04.003
it'll just cost you more money
and time and...

01:00:05.041 --> 01:00:06.131
emotional stress,

01:00:06.208 --> 01:00:08.628
and you'll probably end up
with the same result anyway.

01:00:08.708 --> 01:00:09.708
Right.

01:00:09.958 --> 01:00:12.828
I mean, I agree with that philosophy.
She does too, I'm sure.

01:00:12.916 --> 01:00:15.996
And I always go with the truth,
no matter where that takes us.

01:00:16.333 --> 01:00:18.453
You know, most people in my business
make up the truth

01:00:18.500 --> 01:00:20.020
so they can get where they need to go.

01:00:20.541 --> 01:00:22.671
You're just transactions to them.

01:00:22.750 --> 01:00:24.630
I-I like to think of you as people.

01:00:24.708 --> 01:00:26.498
Oh, okay, good.

01:00:26.583 --> 01:00:28.043
And not just you, her too.

01:00:28.125 --> 01:00:28.955
Yes.

01:00:29.041 --> 01:00:31.171
You know, this can be
a really ugly process.

01:00:31.250 --> 01:00:33.920
But I also believe
it doesn't have to be terrible.

01:00:34.208 --> 01:00:35.578
I'm glad to hear you say that.

01:00:36.125 --> 01:00:37.125
Um...

01:00:37.708 --> 01:00:40.078
I'd love to keep expenses down
as much as possible.

01:00:40.166 --> 01:00:41.166
Of course you do.

